description:
“A month was too long,” I confess. “I was beginning to think I made it all up.”“I know,” he pulls me closer. I try to think of how to say what I want to without coming off as weird. “I mean, we’re friends, right?” I ask. “You don’t have to worry about what you say to me.” “What if there’s nothing I want to say that’s friendly?” Asher lowers his hands and we continue dancing.Little did I know how much my life was about to change, for I am getting a second chance encounter with my celebrity crush, Asher Montgomery. Yes, 
the
 Asher Montgomery, former Let’s Go member, super hot popstar-turned-actor who mysteriously doesn’t make music anymore. AKA the teenage (and current, just don’t tell my boyfriend) love of my life. I'm just praying Asher doesn’t remember the last time we met - when I was a shocked and shy, blabbering and incoherent, hot mess. This is the story on how my world was turned upside down. For I am Elle Harris, and I'm startstuck.{This is a cute, fun, light read, with a HEA}
